headlines.description: — Jaylen Brown scored 22 points and Derek White hit a floater from the foul line with less than a minute left on Sunday to help the Boston Celtics recover after blowing most of a 20-point, first-half lead and beat the Denver Nuggets 110-103.
headlines.shortLinkText: Brown scores 22, Celtics beat Nuggets 110-103 despite 20 points, 14 boards and 9 assists from Jokic

events.name: Portland Trail Blazers at Cleveland Cavaliers

headlines.description: — De'Andre Hunter scored 32 points and made a go-ahead 3-pointer with 30 seconds left in overtime as the Cleveland Cavaliers rallied for a 133-129 win over the Portland Trail Blazers on Sunday to extend their winning streak to 10 and become the first...
headlines.shortLinkText: Hunter scores 32 points and Cavs hold off Blazers 133-129 in OT for 10th straight win, 50th overall

headlines.description: — Aaron Nesmith scored a career-high 27 points, Pascal Siakam added 20 and the Indiana Pacers defeated the Chicago Bulls 127-112 on Sunday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Nesmith scores a career-high 27 points to lead Pacers past Bulls 127-112

events.name: New York Knicks at Miami Heat

headlines.description: — Jalen Brunson scored 31 points and the New York Knicks overcame a 19-point deficit to beat the Miami Heat 116-112 in overtime Sunday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Knicks overcame a 19-point deficit to beat the Heat 116-112 in overtime

headlines.description: — Immanuel Quickley scored 17 of his 24 points in the second half and the Toronto Raptors held on to beat the Orlando Magic 104-102 on Sunday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Quickley's big second half helps Raptors hold off Magic 104-102

events.name: Oklahoma City Thunder at San Antonio Spurs

headlines.description: — Jalen Williams had a career-high 41 points, Shai Gilgeous-Alexander added 31 and the Oklahoma City Thunder beat San Antonio 146-132 on Sunday night, spoiling the Spurs' homecoming following a momentous road trip.
headlines.shortLinkText: Thunder spoil Spurs' homecoming with 146-132 victory behind career-high 41 points by Williams

events.name: New Orleans Pelicans at Utah Jazz

headlines.description: — Kelly Olynyk scored a season-high 26 points and had nine rebounds and the New Orleans Pelicans used a 15-0 fourth-quarter run to defeat the Utah Jazz 128-121 on Sunday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Olynyk scores season-high 26 points as Pelicans use fourth-quarter surge to beat Jazz 128-121

headlines.description: — Anthony Edwards scored 44 points, Julius Randle added 20 in his first game since missing more than a month with an injury and the Minnesota Timberwolves beat the Phoenix Suns 116-98 on Sunday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Edwards scores 44 points, Randle adds 20 in return to help the Timberwolves beat the Suns 116-98

events.name: LA Clippers at Los Angeles Lakers

headlines.description: — Luka Doncic had 29 points and nine assists, LeBron James added 17 points and the Los Angeles Lakers hung on to beat the Los Angeles Clippers for the second time in three days, 108-102 on Sunday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Luka scores 29 points and LeBron adds 17 in the Lakers' 2nd straight win over the Clippers, 108-102
